  "text": "Making selected student subsets public also raises issues of how to choose these students and whether or not public display of their images is acceptable. Given that some of our participants indicated that they try to focus on students not paying attention, this could be controversial. In the TELEP experience [CITATION_1] , for example, many remote participants elected not to display video images because they did not want to be seen multi-tasking in their offices. Public display of student subgroups is also problematic in the case of perceived disproportionate focus on socially charged categories, such as foreign or minority students.",
